The paper deals with typeclass resolution, which is a topic in both programming languages and interactive proof assistants. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories. 

cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category, as the paper deals with a formal procedure for resolving typeclasses, which is a logical problem. 

cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely, as the paper deals with ad-hoc polymorphism, which is a topic in programming languages. 

cs.SE (Software Engineering) is another possible category, as the paper discusses the use of typeclasses in software development. 

cs.CL (Computation and Language) is a less likely category, but still possible, as the paper deals with a language feature (typeclasses) and its implementation. 

cs.PL (Programming Languages) is listed again as a fifth possible category, as it is a broad category that could encompass the topics discussed in the paper.
